1
00:00:10,367 --> 00:00:11,667
<i> Bok, I need to leave.</i>

2
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:13,600
<i>We need to find and catch
everyone who escaped,</i>

3
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:14,833
<i> especially Mando.</i>

4
00:00:14,967 --> 00:00:15,767
<i> Conde!</i>

5
00:00:16,967 --> 00:00:18,133
<i> Bok!</i>

6
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:19,133
<i> Help!</i>

7
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,633
<i>Based on his x-ray
and CT scan results,</i>

8
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:25,567
<i>there were no vital organs
that were hit.</i>

9
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:26,800
<i> Mando escaped?</i>

10
00:00:26,933 --> 00:00:28,600
<i>Yes, Conde, there are three
fugitives now.</i>

11
00:00:28,733 --> 00:00:30,900
<i>Those pimple patch drugs
from earlier,</i>

12
00:00:31,033 --> 00:00:31,833
<i> where did you get them?</i>

13
00:00:31,967 --> 00:00:33,533
<i> In Anika's makeup bag.</i>

14
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:34,567
<i> Anika?</i>

15
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:36,200
<i>You're not putting this on me,
Jhem.</i>

16
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:37,167
<i> Product sample?</i>

17
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:38,533
<i>Who do you think
will believe that?</i>

18
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:41,067
<i>Just stick to the plan, okay?
And everything will be fine.</i>

19
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:44,267
<i>Can you please not join
the search for Mando?</i>

20
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:45,800
<i> Leave that to someone else.</i>

21
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:47,000
<i> It's nice, isn't it?</i>

22
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:48,233
<i>That someone is worried
about you.</i>

23
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:51,700
<i>Meanwhile, no one still cares
about me.</i>

24
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:52,167
<i> Eric?</i>

25
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:53,167
<i> Doc?</i>

26
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:54,800
<i>I just wanted to check
on all of you.</i>

27
00:00:54,933 --> 00:00:57,233
<i>I heard a lot of people
were hurt by what happened.</i>

28
00:00:57,367 --> 00:00:59,267
<i>It's a good thing he wasn't
seriously wounded.</i>

29
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:02,233
<i>Well, I heard he's undergoing
surgery right now.</i>

30
00:01:02,367 --> 00:01:04,167
<i> You're a real animal, Conde.</i>

31
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:05,367
<i> How did you survive?</i>

32
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:09,233
<i> I won't stop until I kill you!</i>

33
00:01:12,467 --> 00:01:13,567
Wait, wait.

34
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:17,067
I remembered that Anika might
not be at their house yet.

35
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,967
Maybe she's still in our
favorite hangout place.

36
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:19,867
Hangout place?

37
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:23,400
Are you sure
that's where Anika is?

38
00:01:23,533 --> 00:01:26,200
Yes, that's where we always
hang out before going home,

39
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:28,967
at the coffee shop
on Padre Burgos Avenue.

40
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:31,133
Okay, let's just do this.

41
00:01:31,267 --> 00:01:36,167
We'll go there. If Anika's
not there, I'll text you.

42
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:37,033
Do you have load on your phone,
Bro?

43
00:01:37,167 --> 00:01:38,567
Because I don't have any.

44
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:41,700
Okay, but I can come with you.

45
00:01:41,867 --> 00:01:43,033
No need.

46
00:01:43,167 --> 00:01:43,900
- That's probably not necessary.
- No need.

47
00:01:44,033 --> 00:01:44,900
Yes, it's okay.

48
00:01:45,033 --> 00:01:46,367
It's okay? Are you sure?

49
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:47,300
It's okay.

50
00:01:47,433 --> 00:01:48,633
But, wait...

51
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:50,867
what are you going to do
with Anika?

52
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,267
Nothing.

53
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:54,033
We just need to find out

54
00:01:54,167 --> 00:01:56,000
where the pimple patch drugs
came from.

55
00:01:56,133 --> 00:01:58,667
And then, we'll report it
to Sir Chito.

56
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,667
Okay. Text me, okay?

57
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:01,800
Yes.

58
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:02,800
Okay, bye.

59
00:02:02,933 --> 00:02:03,567
Okay.

60
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:08,333
So, Bro...

61
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:11,333
Do you think Anika
is really the supplier here?

62
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:13,100
We don't know.

63
00:02:13,233 --> 00:02:14,967
But I have a really
strong feeling

64
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:17,133
that the product came from Jako.

65
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:21,500
If ever, Anika will be
our witness to catch Jako.

66
00:02:21,633 --> 00:02:23,067
You're really good, Bro.

67
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,767
You know, you can be a cop.

68
00:02:26,067 --> 00:02:26,800
Let's go.

69
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:27,667
Let's go.

70
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:31,100
Vice...

71
00:03:04,133 --> 00:03:04,700
Doc...

72
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:09,167
you don't need to beat
around the bush.

73
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:12,633
I know you really came here
for me.

74
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:15,233
I know you're very concerned
about me.

75
00:03:15,367 --> 00:03:18,700
Eric, you know I'm with Glen,
right?

76
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:19,567
Doc...

77
00:03:21,233 --> 00:03:23,767
Sir, I'll leave you two alone
for now.

78
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,567
Excuse me.

79
00:03:27,933 --> 00:03:29,067
Do you love him?

80
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:32,500
Are you here for Faye?

81
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:34,333
No, Vice.

82
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:35,567
That's truth is...

83
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:39,067
Will and I are undercover
agents.

84
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,533
Undercover agents?

85
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:41,500
Yes, Vice.

86
00:03:41,633 --> 00:03:45,433
Is that because of the
pimple patch drugs

87
00:03:45,567 --> 00:03:47,267
that victimized Faye?

88
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:50,400
Yes, Vice, but we're going after
a possible lead.

89
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:53,367
Faye said she got
the pimple patch drugs

90
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,933
from their friend Anika.

91
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,633
Anika?

92
00:03:56,767 --> 00:03:59,233
Do you think she's the supplier?

93
00:03:59,367 --> 00:04:01,433
We're not yet sure about that,
Vice.

94
00:04:02,633 --> 00:04:04,033
I'm Corporal Mariano.

95
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,700
Where is that Anika?

96
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:10,400
We were told that she was
at the coffee shop

97
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:12,100
on Padre Burgos Avenue.

98
00:04:12,233 --> 00:04:14,433
We're going to go there now
to talk to her.

99
00:04:14,567 --> 00:04:16,000
Okay.

100
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:17,600
Update me.

101
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:19,300
I'll go see Faye first.

102
00:04:19,433 --> 00:04:20,767
Okay, Vice, we'll go ahead.

103
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:22,033
- Let's go.
- We'll go ahead.

104
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:27,667
What do you mean?

105
00:04:30,667 --> 00:04:32,733
I mean...

106
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:34,000
do you love him?

107
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:38,800
Because when you love someone...

108
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:41,300
you're happy, right?

109
00:04:43,233 --> 00:04:45,667
But when I saw the two of you,

110
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,667
it didn't seem like
you were happy with him.

111
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:51,800
Eric,

112
00:04:51,933 --> 00:04:53,800
I'm so sorry...

113
00:04:53,933 --> 00:04:56,433
if, somehow, I led you on.

114
00:04:59,733 --> 00:05:01,733
I'm with Glen now,

115
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:05,567
and I think it's better for us,
especially for you...

116
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:07,867
to stop bugging me.

117
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,300
Can Glen stop me?

118
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:11,867
Eric, please.

119
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,467
You don't know Glen.

120
00:05:15,467 --> 00:05:16,900
I'll change my question.

121
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,433
Are you happy with him?

122
00:05:38,667 --> 00:05:42,833
Oh my, the escape of the
prisoners is a huge mess.

123
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:45,300
That's why we can't talk
to Sir Tonyo.

124
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:47,500
Well, let's just be careful.

125
00:05:47,633 --> 00:05:49,767
Let's get some information
from Anika,

126
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:52,967
then we'll report it
to Boss Tonyo later.

127
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,033
Let's go, Will.

128
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,167
Hey, Bro.

129
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:57,700
Is there a problem, Bro?

130
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,033
I'm sorry, Vince.

131
00:06:03,767 --> 00:06:06,300
I can't join you
on our mission anymore.

132
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:07,500
Why, Bro?

133
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:08,733
What happened?

134
00:06:08,867 --> 00:06:10,300
My dad is gone.

135
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:13,633
I need to go back to Manila.

136
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:18,633
Sorry, Bro.

137
00:06:18,767 --> 00:06:20,200
My condolences.

138
00:06:22,067 --> 00:06:24,600
I'll contact my batchmate.

139
00:06:24,733 --> 00:06:27,433
He used to work as an undercover
agent under Lieutenant Conde.

140
00:06:27,567 --> 00:06:28,733
I'll ask him to sub me.

141
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,267
Good luck, Bro.

142
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,700
I hope you can solve this case.

143
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:35,933
Okay, Bro.

144
00:06:37,567 --> 00:06:39,233
I'll do it.

145
00:06:39,367 --> 00:06:40,733
We'll solve the case.

146
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:41,900
Take care, okay?

147
00:06:52,967 --> 00:06:54,667
Tonyo's lucky, right?

148
00:06:56,433 --> 00:06:58,567
How did he get lucky, Sir?
He got shot.

149
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:04,733
He's lucky because someone
is watching over him.

150
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:09,867
Me.

151
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,233
You thought it was you,
didn't you?

152
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,133
What's the update?

153
00:07:22,267 --> 00:07:23,600
Confirmed.

154
00:07:23,733 --> 00:07:25,700
Five prisoners escaped,

155
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:27,800
and Mandong Warak
was among them.

156
00:07:27,933 --> 00:07:31,100
Sir, we should hunt them down.

157
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:33,433
That's really going to be
our mandate, Garcia.

158
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:39,633
But let's make sure Conde's
condition is stable first.

159
00:07:39,767 --> 00:07:42,033
I'll add more guards here

160
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:46,300
because we know that Mandong
Warak is very angry with Conde.

161
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,667
Excuse me, Sir.

162
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,733
Lieutenant Conde's surgery
is already done.

163
00:07:53,867 --> 00:07:55,733
We'll be bringing him
into the room now.

164
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:57,000
Thank you very much.

165
00:08:12,767 --> 00:08:17,567
Dante, I think I now know
who Monty gave my products to.

166
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,633
We need to cover our tracks.

167
00:08:36,567 --> 00:08:37,533
Vince?

168
00:08:41,067 --> 00:08:43,267
I'm the one Will asked to sub
for him during your operation.

169
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:46,467
Corporal Allen Matibag.

170
00:08:49,167 --> 00:08:51,667
Vince De Leon,
professional undercover.

171
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:02,200
Since you're new...

172
00:09:04,233 --> 00:09:06,933
I'll be in charge
of this operation.

173
00:09:07,067 --> 00:09:08,100
Got it?

174
00:09:08,233 --> 00:09:09,533
No problem.

175
00:09:09,667 --> 00:09:11,800
I'm just here to help.

176
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:15,667
But if there's an emergency,
you'll listen to me

177
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:18,100
because I'm still the policeman
between the two of us.

178
00:09:18,233 --> 00:09:19,033
Got it?

179
00:09:20,533 --> 00:09:21,767
Okay.

180
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:24,900
I'll explain everything
as we walk.

181
00:09:25,033 --> 00:09:25,900
Let's go.

182
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:36,067
<i>You can tell them that you just
got the pimple patch from...</i>

183
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,100
<i> from the store.</i>

184
00:09:37,233 --> 00:09:38,267
<i>A product sample,
something like that.</i>

185
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:42,567
I can't. I don't know.
I can't, Jhem. I'm so sorry.

186
00:09:53,533 --> 00:09:54,367
Anika?

187
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:56,400
Who are you?

188
00:09:56,533 --> 00:09:57,367
There's Anika.

189
00:09:58,567 --> 00:09:59,567
Let's go, Bro.

190
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,100
Anika, right?

191
00:10:03,967 --> 00:10:04,767
Come with me.

192
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:06,233
Why should I go with you?
Who are you?

193
00:10:06,367 --> 00:10:07,600
I don't know you.

194
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:09,067
Who's the guy she's with?

195
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,633
I don't know either, Bro.

196
00:10:10,767 --> 00:10:12,067
That's the first time I saw him.

197
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,167
It must have something to do
with the pimple patch.

198
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:15,233
Aren't you coming?

199
00:10:17,133 --> 00:10:20,000
Come with me if you don't want
to get hurt.

200
00:10:20,133 --> 00:10:20,833
Let's go.

201
00:10:24,967 --> 00:10:26,267
Hey, Bro, he took Anika.

202
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,600
Let's go, let's follow them!

203
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:34,533
- Let's go!
- Let's go.

204
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:45,333
Wait, Bro.

205
00:10:45,467 --> 00:10:46,667
We can't catch up with them.

206
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:49,067
There!

207
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,167
- Get one!
- Let's go!

208
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:50,967
Let's go, let's go.

209
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:54,600
Bro, our bike!

210
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:55,333
Hey, our bike...

211
00:10:55,467 --> 00:10:56,500
Hey, that's our bike! Hey!

212
00:10:56,633 --> 00:10:58,033
Give us back our bikes!

213
00:10:58,167 --> 00:11:00,133
Hey! That's our bike!
Give that back!

214
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:17,967
Who's your supplier
for the pimple patch drugs?

215
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:21,167
I don't know anything
about those pimple patch drugs!

216
00:11:21,300 --> 00:11:23,667
I just got them from the mall!

217
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:27,933
If you don't tell me
who your supplier is,

218
00:11:28,067 --> 00:11:28,933
you'll be dead.

219
00:11:29,067 --> 00:11:31,600
If I tell you,
will you let me go?

220
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:33,633
I'm not the pusher.

221
00:11:33,767 --> 00:11:36,367
I promise, I'm only a user.

222
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:37,733
Let you go?

223
00:11:37,867 --> 00:11:40,600
It depends on whether you
tell me who your supplier is.

224
00:11:40,733 --> 00:11:45,700
It's Jhem, my classmate.

225
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:47,633
She's the one
you're looking for.

226
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:48,733
She's the one...

227
00:11:48,867 --> 00:11:51,100
She's the one who sells
the pimple patch drugs

228
00:11:51,233 --> 00:11:52,467
at our university.

229
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:54,800
Call her.

230
00:11:54,933 --> 00:11:57,500
Tell her to meet you
at Malindang Park.

231
00:11:59,767 --> 00:12:04,633
Make sure she comes, or else
I'll blow your skull off!

232
00:12:12,167 --> 00:12:12,967
Hello?

233
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:13,867
Hello, Jhem?

234
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:17,533
We have a problem.

235
00:12:17,667 --> 00:12:19,267
Can we meet?

236
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,300
Here.

237
00:12:25,433 --> 00:12:27,200
Drink lots of water.

238
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:29,033
That'll help.

239
00:12:29,167 --> 00:12:31,333
Sorry, Glen. I didn't know...

240
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:33,933
No, it's not your fault.
Don't worry about it.

241
00:12:40,567 --> 00:12:42,300
<i>I have Anika now.
I'll update you, Boss.</i>

242
00:12:42,433 --> 00:12:46,200
Glen, what's going to happen
to Anika?

243
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:49,233
I got those patches from her.

244
00:12:50,567 --> 00:12:52,700
I already told Sir Chito.

245
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,200
Well...

246
00:12:56,433 --> 00:12:57,800
don't worry about her.

247
00:12:57,933 --> 00:12:58,967
She'll be fine.

248
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:00,733
Okay?

249
00:13:10,033 --> 00:13:10,767
Faye...

250
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,167
Faye, how are you?

251
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:13,600
I'm getting better, Daddy.

252
00:13:13,733 --> 00:13:15,000
That's good.

253
00:13:15,133 --> 00:13:17,000
I just need to do
some water therapy.

254
00:13:17,133 --> 00:13:17,833
Good.

255
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:25,367
Glen, let me know once
the supplier is caught, okay?

256
00:13:25,533 --> 00:13:28,600
I'll make sure that
they will all rot in prison.

257
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:47,800
Major, we've removed the bullet
from Sir Tonyo's body.

258
00:13:47,933 --> 00:13:49,967
He just needs to rest
and recover.

259
00:13:51,433 --> 00:13:52,333
Thank you very much, Doc.

260
00:13:52,467 --> 00:13:53,167
Thank you.

261
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:54,867
Nurse, let's go.

262
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:08,133
Garcia...

263
00:14:09,433 --> 00:14:11,133
stay here for now.

264
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,000
Keep an eye on Conde.

265
00:14:13,133 --> 00:14:15,567
We need to go back
to the station

266
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:19,567
to discuss how the manhunt
operation will go.

267
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:20,900
Yes, Sir.

268
00:14:21,033 --> 00:14:23,100
I'll take care of Conde for now.

269
00:14:23,233 --> 00:14:26,000
I'll let you know
when there's an update.

270
00:14:27,267 --> 00:14:31,467
And I'll go to the police
station once everything's okay.

271
00:14:31,633 --> 00:14:32,433
Okay.

272
00:14:32,567 --> 00:14:34,800
Enriquez, let's go.

273
00:14:40,267 --> 00:14:41,667
Don't worry.

274
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:43,500
I'll take care of Tonyo.

275
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,333
Enriquez...

276
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:55,067
don't forget what I told you
earlier.

277
00:14:56,667 --> 00:15:00,400
Just leave the search
for Mando to them.

278
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,533
Operation Manhunt starts now.

279
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:22,533
Review all the detailed profiles
I gave you.

280
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:27,233
And let's make sure that these
guys are brought back to prison

281
00:15:27,367 --> 00:15:29,433
before they hurt anyone else.

282
00:15:30,867 --> 00:15:32,267
Sir...

283
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,200
Yes, Enriquez?

284
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,533
You can assign Mando to me.

285
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:38,033
I'll take care of him.

286
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:47,533
Are you sure?

287
00:15:48,733 --> 00:15:50,900
Mando is the most dangerous
of them all.

288
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,000
I'm quite certain, Sir.

289
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:57,900
Okay.

290
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:02,133
Keep your communication lines
open.

291
00:16:02,267 --> 00:16:06,400
Report all information you get
to me.

292
00:16:06,533 --> 00:16:07,467
Dismissed.

293
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,033
Here are the pictures
of the four prisoners

294
00:16:16,167 --> 00:16:18,300
who escaped from Calabari
Prison.

295
00:16:18,433 --> 00:16:20,967
All residents of Calabari
and neighboring towns

296
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:22,367
are being warned.

297
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:24,700
If anyone sees one of them,

298
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:27,367
they can report it immediately
to the number you see

299
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:28,400
on the screen.

300
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:34,167
Dude, this is their car.

301
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:35,133
Yes, that's the one.

302
00:16:41,933 --> 00:16:44,233
Good thing we saw it.
Where could they be?

303
00:16:44,367 --> 00:16:45,700
I have a bad feeling about this.

304
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:47,333
We might need backup.

305
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:49,600
Negative, Bro.

306
00:16:49,733 --> 00:16:52,233
The police are busy right now
because of the fugitives.

307
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,367
If you need backup, Bro,
I know someone.

308
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,300
Wait a minute.

309
00:17:00,933 --> 00:17:02,400
Dude, wait a minute.

310
00:17:02,533 --> 00:17:03,533
Someone's calling? Who's that?

311
00:17:03,667 --> 00:17:04,200
Hey, it's Vince!

312
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:05,633
Hey, it's Vince.

313
00:17:05,767 --> 00:17:07,367
Vince, Bro!

314
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:11,067
How's life being an undercover
agent? How's it going?

315
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,600
Bro, I need your help.

316
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:15,133
You need to get
to Malindang Park right now.

317
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:16,833
Bro, hurry up.

318
00:17:16,967 --> 00:17:19,167
Malindang Park?
Okay, we'll go there.

319
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,467
- Malindang, Bro.
- Why?

320
00:17:23,633 --> 00:17:24,767
Come on, let's find them.

321
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:25,433
Let's go.

322
00:17:26,967 --> 00:17:28,767
What's our first move, Ma'am?

323
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:30,767
We need to talk
to someone first.

324
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:33,033
For sure, he'll be a big help.

325
00:17:33,167 --> 00:17:35,300
Why did you choose Mando, Ma'am?

326
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,367
Why?

327
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,333
Enriquez...

328
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:43,600
can I talk to you?

329
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:46,000
Okay, Sir.

330
00:17:47,067 --> 00:17:48,033
Noble...

331
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:56,633
I heard you took Mando's case.

332
00:17:59,167 --> 00:18:01,867
Didn't Conde talk to you
about that?

333
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,100
What's with you?

334
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:07,667
It's obvious that the man
is worried about you.

335
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:11,667
Good for you, someone
is worried about you.

336
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:12,767
As for me...

337
00:18:16,633 --> 00:18:20,933
Sir, we know that Sir Tonyo
is Mando's target, right?

338
00:18:21,067 --> 00:18:22,700
Right now, he can't do anything

339
00:18:22,867 --> 00:18:24,333
because he knows there are
a lot of police officers

340
00:18:24,467 --> 00:18:25,533
at the hospital.

341
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:28,167
But I won't wait for that, Sir.
I'll move now.

342
00:18:33,467 --> 00:18:33,967
Mayor.

343
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:34,867
Good evening to you all.

344
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:35,400
Good evening.

345
00:18:35,533 --> 00:18:36,033
Mayor.

346
00:18:36,167 --> 00:18:38,400
Where is Major Flores?

347
00:18:38,533 --> 00:18:40,167
Okay, Mayor. I'll just call him.

348
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:40,900
Okay.

349
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:48,733
I beg you, Sir...

350
00:18:48,867 --> 00:18:52,833
please don't tell Sir Tonyo
about this.

351
00:18:52,967 --> 00:18:54,700
He might get even more stressed.

352
00:18:56,867 --> 00:18:59,300
Okay, be careful.

353
00:18:59,433 --> 00:19:00,433
Thank you, Sir.

354
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,833
Enriquez...

355
00:19:02,967 --> 00:19:04,667
be careful of Mando, okay?

356
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:05,467
Yes, Sir.

357
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,300
Thank you.

358
00:19:07,433 --> 00:19:08,200
Bobby.

359
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,600
Mayor, what are you doing here?

360
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:13,933
Well, I'll just talk
to Major Flores.

361
00:19:15,233 --> 00:19:17,333
You, where are you going?

362
00:19:17,467 --> 00:19:19,700
We have a manhunt operation.

363
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:21,333
Take Conde with you, okay?

364
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:23,767
I'll feel more at ease
if you're with him.

365
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:26,433
Sir Conde is in the hospital.

366
00:19:26,567 --> 00:19:27,767
Oh, why?

367
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:32,500
He was shot by a fugitive,
but he's recovering.

368
00:19:32,667 --> 00:19:34,567
He's recovering in the hospital.

369
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:37,900
Just call me if you need
anything, okay?

370
00:19:38,033 --> 00:19:39,333
Okay, take care, my child.

371
00:19:39,467 --> 00:19:41,167
Yes, thank you.

372
00:19:41,300 --> 00:19:42,300
Okay.

373
00:19:50,667 --> 00:19:51,733
Mayor!

374
00:19:51,867 --> 00:19:52,933
- Good evening.
- Major.

375
00:19:54,433 --> 00:19:56,267
I would like to talk to you.

376
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,933
Let's go to the office, Mayor.

377
00:19:58,067 --> 00:19:58,767
Okay.

378
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:08,000
What's going on, Major?

379
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,100
We're still investigating,
Mayor.

380
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:13,633
But I assure you

381
00:20:13,767 --> 00:20:15,133
that we're on top of everything.

382
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:18,533
Including the pimple patch drugs
supplier

383
00:20:18,667 --> 00:20:19,733
at your daughter's school.

384
00:20:20,867 --> 00:20:22,400
How's Faye?

385
00:20:22,533 --> 00:20:24,100
Faye's okay, Major.

386
00:20:25,533 --> 00:20:27,633
Now, I just can't quite
figure it out...

387
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:31,333
Another crime has occured here
in Calabari,

388
00:20:31,467 --> 00:20:37,367
like this pimple patch drugs
and the escape of the criminals.

389
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:40,433
Do you think, Mayor...

390
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:42,067
there's a connection between
the two?

391
00:20:44,167 --> 00:20:49,300
Because prisoners can't escape
just like that!

392
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:53,533
I think they have a proper
connection.

393
00:20:53,667 --> 00:20:58,600
That's why cases like this need
to be looked at carefully.

394
00:20:58,733 --> 00:21:03,333
So, Major, you should broaden
your perspective on this case.

395
00:21:04,567 --> 00:21:08,400
I think we have a new enemy.

396
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,933
<i> Update?</i>

397
00:21:46,733 --> 00:21:49,133
<i>Your father is in the station,
talking to Major.</i>

398
00:21:49,267 --> 00:21:54,567
<i>Just let him be.
He's got nothing.</i>

399
00:22:25,533 --> 00:22:26,900
<i> Go hide.</i>

400
00:22:27,033 --> 00:22:29,100
Your face is all over the news.

401
00:22:29,233 --> 00:22:31,867
Go to the address
that I sent you.

402
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,033
That's where your next
assignment is.

403
00:22:34,167 --> 00:22:35,667
I'll do that next time, Boss.

404
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:37,533
I just need to take care
of something.

405
00:22:37,667 --> 00:22:39,200
Are you crazy?

406
00:22:39,333 --> 00:22:40,767
If you get caught,

407
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:43,533
<i>the money I spent to get you out
will be wasted.</i>

408
00:22:43,667 --> 00:22:45,700
Yeah, I know that already, Boss.

409
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,867
Don't drink too much coffee.

410
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,467
<i> This is Mando.</i>

411
00:22:49,633 --> 00:22:51,833
I'll work on that.

412
00:22:51,967 --> 00:22:53,533
I just need to finish this.

413
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:07,100
My contact said that Rodel
Pacheco's former residence

414
00:23:07,233 --> 00:23:08,300
is in this village.

415
00:23:08,433 --> 00:23:09,933
We need to catch him right away.

416
00:23:10,067 --> 00:23:11,833
He might hurt someone else.

417
00:23:11,967 --> 00:23:12,567
Son of a...

418
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:13,633
- Come on!
- Hurry!

419
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:15,400
Jhem, tell him where
the pimple patches are.

420
00:23:15,533 --> 00:23:16,933
Tell him, please.

421
00:23:17,067 --> 00:23:18,567
I know you can't kill me,

422
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:21,033
unless I tell you where the
remaining items are, right?

423
00:23:21,167 --> 00:23:23,700
I can't kill you,
but I can kill her.

424
00:23:23,867 --> 00:23:24,800
Anika!

425
00:23:24,933 --> 00:23:27,400
Too bad, Conde, your girlfriend
is already dead.

426
00:23:27,533 --> 00:23:31,033
Who can I use to get you out
of the hospital?

427
00:23:31,167 --> 00:23:33,767
We've long accepted
that Tonyo loves someone else.

428
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:34,400
Who?

429
00:23:34,533 --> 00:23:36,433
It's Ma'am Bobby.
